South Korea's program is considered a success in controlling the outbreak, although it did not quarantine entire cities. South Korean society was initially divided over President Moon Jae-in's response to the crisis.
Many Koreans have signed petitions calling for Moon's impeachment for the government's poor handling of the outbreak or praising his response.
On 23 March, South Korea recorded its lowest daily case count in four weeks.
On 29 March, it was announced that from 1 April, all arrivals from abroad would be quarantined for two weeks.
According to media reports, on 1 April, South Korea received requests for assistance in the detection of the virus from 121 different countries.
