Researchers at the Montreal Heart Institute in Canada are currently investigating the role of colchicine in reducing inflammation and pulmonary complications in patients with moderate symptoms of COVID-19.
The COLCORONA study is recruiting 6,000 adults aged 40 years and older who have been diagnosed positive for COVID-19 and have mild symptoms that do not require hospitalization.
