On 12 March 2020, Medicago, a biotechnology company in Quebec, Quebec, announced that it had developed a coronavirus-like particle with partial funding from Canadian health research institutes.
The vaccine candidate is currently undergoing laboratory research, with human trials scheduled for July or August 2020.
Earlier this week, The Guardian reported that US President Donald Trump offered CureVac large sums of money for exclusive access to the COVID-19 vaccine, which sparked the German government's protest.
On 17 March 2020, the US pharmaceutical company Pfizer announced a partnership with the German company BioNTech for the joint development of a mRNA vaccine.
